      "language": "language primarily spoken in {a}",
      "demonym": "name for someone from {a}",
      "continent": "world region containing {a}"
    },
    "operand_slots": ["a"],
    "desinence_pair": ["language", "demonym"],
    "note": "LEXICAL paraphrases of relations.json: the '{op} of {a}' unit itself is replaced (different content words, different syntax around the operand), not just the frame. Same operands and answers as relations.json, so operator directions built on formulation A (relations.json) can be tested on formulation B (this file) directly -- the cross-lexicalization test that separates 'direction of the relation' from 'direction of the phrasing'."
